<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10127258>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Propodeum. A. Entedon sylvestris Szelényi, 1981, ♀ (used for SEM). B. Entedon crassiscapus Erdös, 1944, ♀ (used for SEM). C. Entedon magnificus (Girault & Dodd, 1913), ♀ (SANC). D. Xiphentedon neserorum sp. nov., ♀ (used for SEM). E. Pediobius ropalidiae (Risbec, 1958), ♀ (paratype, MRAC). F. Colpixys gigas Bouček, 1972, ♀ (paratype, NHMUK). Abbreviations: lc = lateral channel on sides of median carina; lp = lateral plica; ls = lateral sulcus of propodeum; mc = median carina; mf = median furrow; msc = metascutellum; mstr = median strip; smc = submedian carinae; spt = spiracular tubercle on propodeum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10127258/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10127276>
    dc:description "Fig. 9. A, C–D. Colpixys necator Waterston, 1916 (NHMUK). B. C. eburnus sp. nov. (paratype, Ivory Coast; CBGP). E–F. C. gigas Bouček, 1972 (paratype, Ghana; NHMUK). A–B. Propodeum. C–D, F. Axillula. E. Head in dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10127276/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10127278>
    dc:description "Fig. 10. Colpixys gigas Bouček, 1972, paratypes (Ghana; USNM). A–B. Habitus, ♀ (A) and ♂ (B). C. ♀, head, mesosoma and anterior part of metasoma." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10127278/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

